params._defaultPoolFee: Default Uniswap V3 pool fee (e.g., 3000 for 0.3%)

params.from: The user whose tokens are being deposited
params.inputAsset: The asset provided by the user
params.minAmountOut: Minimum amount after swap (if inputAsset != targetAsset)
params.targetAsset: The strategy's asset to deposit into

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

reallocate(uint8,address,address,address.details: Sequence: report() -> compute assets from shares -> withdraw -> swap -> deposit

params.minAmountOut: Minimum amount expected after the swap
params.shares: Amount of source strategy shares to migrate

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

params.assets: Amount of strategyAsset to withdraw from the strategy
params.minAmountOut: Minimum amount after swap (if strategyAsset != outputAsset)
params.outputAsset: The asset to send to the receiver
params.owner: The owner of the strategy shares (must have approved this contract to burn shares)
params.strategyAsset: The asset handled by the source strategy

returns.amountOut: Final output amount sent to receiver

depositERC20(uint8,address,address,uint2.notice: Deposit ERC20 on behalf of a user, optionally swap to target asset, then deposit into the (profile, targetAsset) strategy

harvestProfile(uint8).notice: Harvest yield from all strategies in a specific profile

harvestStrategy(address).notice: Harvest yield from a specific strategy

permitShares(address,address,uint256,uin.notice: EIP-2612 permit for strategy share token, enabling this orchestrator to manage shares

reallocate(uint8,address,address,address.notice: Reallocate a user's position across assets within the same profile

setStrategy(uint8,address,address).notice: Register a YDS strategy for a given (profile, asset)

withdrawERC20(uint8,address,address,uint.notice: Withdraw from a (profile, asset) strategy on behalf of a user to a desired asset (optional swap), transfer to receiver
